"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-paris-2024-olympics-withdrawals-best-moments-recap\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.999931050147738, \"rank\": 6.894389521698583e-05, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbParis 2024 Olympics withdrawals: Best moments RECAP!\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.999931050147738, \"rank\": 6.894389521698583e-05, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surely one of the best Olympic Games in history?\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Olympics were a glorious concoction of sporting excellence, patriotism and pure, unadulterated emotion.\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 318, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's a recap of the finest moments because life feels a little meaningless without it.\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bayanda Walaza, Bradley Nkoana, Shaun Maswanganyi and Akani Simbine deservedly got their hands on silver at the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 533, \"end\": 540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Braves_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.9862820620345453, \"rank\": 0.012448836585371627, \"text\": \"Bradley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Braves_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Braves_men's_basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 549, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"score\": 0.9999968692872139, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaun Maswanganyi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\"}, {\"begin\": 571, \"end\": 584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This after a sensational performance in the 4x100m relay final.\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Simbine had a bit of work to do in the final leg after an immensely competitive race, but the 30-year-old got it done and finally stopped some much-deserved silverware on the biggest stage.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That must taste sweet for a man who's made the solo 100m final at three consecutive Olympic Games but narrowly missed out on the podium each time.\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Less than a week ago, he lost out on a medal by one-hundredth of a second in the biggest race in world sprinting.\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1158, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the fastest event of its type in history.\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shout-out also to teenagers Nkoana and Walaza.\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latter chose to forego exams to compete for his country in Paris.\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1313023131559917e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"23-year-old Shaun Maswanganyi also has a massive future in sprinting.\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1338, \"end\": 1355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"score\": 0.9999968692872139, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaun Maswanganyi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tatjana Smith became the most decorated Olympian in South African historywith her haul oftwo medalsin Paris.\", \"from\": 1397, \"to\": 1505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1437, \"end\": 1445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999998501466619, \"rank\": 1.498533135741221e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1499, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1313023131559917e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She claimed gold in the 100m breaststroke and silver in the 200m event, an exact reversal of her antics in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7081321277880643, \"rank\": 0.41216576126710847, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other Team SA medallists in 2024 areAlan Hatherlywho\\u00a0won bronze in the men's Mountain Bike (MTB) cross-country race; South Africa's first Olympic cycling medal since 1956, some 68 years ago, and theRugby Sevens sidewho claimed bronze by beating Australia.\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0124650588593728e-31, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mountain_bike\", \"score\": 0.9999999999881766, \"rank\": 1.174129668624947e-11, \"text\": \"MTB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mountain_bike\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mountain_bike\"}, {\"begin\": 1869, \"end\": 1878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9959483668049286, \"rank\": 0.0036549817092530893, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 4x100m relay side and Jo-Ane van Dyk's silver in the women's javelin took Team SA's totalmedal tally to SIX.A gold, three silvers and two bronzes.\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 2030, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jo-Ane van Dyk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\"}, {\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0124650588593728e-31, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Outside of a South African perspective, there were so many stellar performances to cherish in Paris.\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2126, \"end\": 2131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1313023131559917e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"21-year-oldLetsile Tebogo's win in the 200m finalwas the first gold medal in Botswana's history at the games.\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2210, \"end\": 2218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.800697294088919e-14, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was also the fifth-fastest time in the history of the event, not only at the Olympics but anywhere on the planet.\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Legendary American gymnast Simone Biles claimed three golds and a silver, taking her overall medal tally at the Olympic Games to 11 (seven gold, two silver, two bronze) across three editions.\", \"from\": 2360, \"to\": 2551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2370, \"end\": 2378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999981226273463, \"rank\": 1.8699819277119044e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2387, \"end\": 2399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the pool, French golden boy Leon Marchand, still only 22 years old, won four golds and a bronze.\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2565, \"end\": 2571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7621937645337928, \"rank\": 0.17796436952528924, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9981855347747843, \"rank\": 0.0018121661434243401, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like Tebogo, we will see more of him in 2028 and beyond.\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch distance runner Sifan Hassan did the unthinkable by winning bronze over 5000m and 10000m and then entering the marathon on the final day of the games.\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2710, \"end\": 2715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9437009759850884, \"rank\": 0.047628353738761925, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2732, \"end\": 2744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sifan Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won that in an Olympic record time (2:22:55), just for good measure.\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 2939, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was easily one of the greatest marathons in Olympic history with the top three separated by only 15 seconds.\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 3051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ethiopia's Tigst Assefa was only three seconds behind Hassan in a sprint finish to claim silver.\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3052, \"end\": 3060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999996927286264, \"rank\": 3.0725548041583894e-07, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 3106, \"end\": 3112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hassan_I_of_Morocco\", \"score\": 0.6974434415059532, \"rank\": 0.37666305049826254, \"text\": \"Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hassan_I_of_Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hassan_I_of_Morocco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cian Oldknow (32nd) was the best South African performer in a superb time of 2:30:29.\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3149, \"end\": 3153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cian\", \"score\": 0.9999999278238673, \"rank\": 7.217600516917689e-08, \"text\": \"Cian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Irvette van Zyl\\u00a0finished\\u00a037th\\u00a0in\\u00a02:31:14 and the legendary Gerda Steyn finished 45th with a time of 2:32:51.\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3235, \"end\": 3250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvette_van_Zyl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Irvette van Zyl\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvette_van_Zyl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvette_van_Zyl\"}, {\"begin\": 3294, \"end\": 3305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerda_Steyn\", \"score\": 0.9999998978501078, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gerda Steyn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerda_Steyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerda_Steyn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.com.\", \"from\": 3345, \"to\": 3443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, you can also send a WhatsApp to 060 011 021 1.\", \"from\": 3444, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3475, \"end\": 3483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\", \"score\": 0.9888640853747763, \"rank\": 0.011261319720177953, \"text\": \"WhatsApp\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow@TheSAnews on XandThe South African on Facebookfor your social fix.\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3575, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring!\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3577, \"end\": 3580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"score\": 0.9953262852252959, \"rank\": 0.004695